==English==
===Etymology===
From the movie industry, where it was customary to end a scene or session of filming by closing off light to the camera, sometimes for dramatic effect, but often as a pracical measure.
===Verb===
'''[[fade]] to [[black]]'''

#(''cinema''): To end a [[film]] or a [[scene]] of a [[flim]] by causing the [[image]] to disappear and become [[black]].